David Koller
David Koller
David Koller is a research assistant at the
   Graphics, Visualization, and Usability Center
in the
   College of Computing
at the
   Georgia Institute of Technology
(which was recently rated the top computer science graphics and HCI graduate program
in the nation!).
He is involved with the
   Virtual Environments Research Group
,
and is currently working on a project integrating
GIS applications and virtual environments for
military visualization and simulation.
Background
Dave spent the first 21 years of his life at and around
   Purdue University
in West Lafayette, Indiana.  He graduated from Purdue in 1994 with a B.S.E. in
Systems Engineering
and a B.S. in
   Computer Science
.  Dave then moved to
   Atlanta
to work at the
   GVU Center,
and intends to begin study soon on a Ph.D. in Computer Science.
